<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 8:36PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Blaine
County through 900 PM MDT...
At 835 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Harlem, or 26 miles east of Chinook, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Blaine
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
